         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">August ¶  ¶ Sir. ¶  ¶ Herewith I have the honor to hand you a sketch of the pigeon which you kindly promised to send Mr J. B. Stair of Broadmeadows. ¶ At a Council meeting of the Acclimatisation Socie...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.08.06<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Sprigg</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 62/560, unit 1, p. 361, VPRS 2225 outward letter press copy books, Acclimatisation Society of Victoria, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">The letter press book does not show the day or year, but the letters<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">before</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">after</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it are dated to 6 August 1862, and this letter is therefore dated to the same date.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>August<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith I have the honor to hand you a sketch of the pigeon which you kindly promised to send Mr J. B. Stair of Broadmeadows.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At a Council meeting of the Acclimatisation Society of Victoria held on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>5 August 1862, 'A letter was read from The Revd J. B. Stair of Broadmeadows addressed to the Vice President concerning the pigeon of which a sketch had been sent by His Excellency. Dr Mueller was requested to reply and to forward to Mr Stair one of the copies which have been made of this bird.' (Unit 1, p. 224, VPRS 2223,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Public Record Office, Victoria).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">The sketch<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">sketch furnished by Governor Barkly</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'of the pigeon that is supposed to be an inhabitant of the Navigator Islands'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">had been laid before the Council meeting held on 29 July a (Argus, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>31 July 1862, p. 4</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>As this is the only copy left here the Council will request that Mr Stair return it at his convenience.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At a Council meeting on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>12 August 1862, 'Letters were laid before the Council by the Vice President which he had received from the Revd J. B. Stair, clergyman at Broadmeadows concerning the pigeon from the Navigator<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">Islands<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">[the name given by Bougainville and used by missionaries for the Samoa</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">b archipelago]</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>of which enquiries are being made by His Excellency Sir Henry Barkly. Mr Stair who resided on these islands for many years at once recognied the sketh furnished by the Zoological<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Society of London as a drawing of the "Manu Mea" or red bird of Samoa. Mr Stair states that these birds are very scarce and pointed out the best way in his opinion to procure them — copies of which the Secretary was requested to send Mr Williams and inform him that the Society would be happy to defray any expense he might be put to in procuring the bird.' (Unit 1, p. 227, VPRS 2223,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Public Record Office, Victoria).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">'Mr Williams' is probably John C. Williams,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">long term<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">British Consul in Samoa</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from 1858 (Watson (1918), p.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">33</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I would also venture to request that you will inform me of the name of the British Consul at Suez so that I may write to him about the Angora goats, as proposed by yourself.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">x-ref.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">May nit have been written, or even in Council meeting</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most Obedt Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Geo Sprigg</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Secretary</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">To Ferdinand Mueller Esqr .D. Ph.D. FR.S.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Government Botanist</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>&amp;c</p>
         </div>
